isease."  Check out the full link to this article here! https://www.apa.org/monitor/2013/11/music  This is why we are choosing to hook you up with the best sounds out there to help you de-stress, unwind as well as promoting focus and studying. (There's music for it all) Whether you like chill ambient music, nature sounds, and or funky piano or hip hop tunes, these playlists are for you!  Bonus: Most videos are aesthetically pleasing, so put them on full screen and have them play in the background while you're doing your thing!      Google Form:  Share Your Favorite Music With Us Here!       The Power of Music!   Check out these videos to learn about the power of music and how it can positively affect your wellbeing!       Your Brain on Music           Music to Unwind and De-stress   Check out these videos and their aesthetic video backgrounds to help lower your heart rate and unwind. Play this music whenever you want to escape reality and relax!       To Lower Your Heart Rate: Relaxing Sounds           Lower Your Heart Rate: Piano sounds           Relaxing Music for Stress Relief. Soothing Music Meditation           For Those Who Like Nature: Soothing Waterfall With Forest Birds           Fan of the Rain? : Soft Rain Sounds           Rain Sounds: With Tibetian Bowl           Studying   Check out these relaxing videos to help you study and focus. Nothing’s better than creating alpha waves when studying!       Study Music to Concentrate- Improve Focus           Study Music: Alpha waves and Concentration           Live: Hip hop Study beats          Modified on April 27, 2020                 UIC Logo        Wellness Center          Contact   Suite 238 750 S Halsted Street  Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 413-2120  wellnesscenter@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  L